# How to run Cypress from Windows 10 + WSL
1. [Install Node.js](https://nodejs.org/en/)
1. [Install XMing](http://www.straightrunning.com/XmingNotes/)
1. Disabled Windows firewall (sigh, it appears to interfere with the network interface from WSL distro connecting to XMing)
*TBD opening a specific port should also work*
1. From Windows run XLaunch
  1. Click through the wizard with defaults except for:
    * Select the checkbox for "Disable access control"
1. Open WSL
1. Navigate to directory where you cloned this repo
1. `npm install`
1. `npx cypress open`
